The '''Southern Appalachian Repertory Theatre''' (SART) is a [[Non-profit organization|not-for-profit]] [[Summer stock theatre|summer stock]] [[theatre company]] that performs in the Owen Theatre at [[Mars Hill College]] in [[Mars Hill, North Carolina]].  It also hosts an annual playwright's conference known as ScriptFEST.  It was founded in 1975 by Jim "T" Thomas, Chairman of the [[Fine art|Fine Arts]] Department of Mars Hill College.  The current [[Artistic director|Artistic Director]] is Bill Gregg, who also teaches theatre at Mars Hill College.  It combines the performing talents of Equity Actors, local professionals and students from the college.

